definition.value: An ammonium betaine that is the conjugate base of choline hydrogen sulfate, obtained by deprotonation of the sulfate OH group.
A member of the class of indenes that is 2,4,5,7a-tetrahydro-1H-indene substituted by methyl groups at positions 1, 4, 4 and 7a and by an oxo group at position 2.
